SUMMARY:Bowling Night - North Jersey
DESCRIPTION:North Jersey Bowling\, Volleyball\, Tennis And More (BVT)\nThi
 s is an event for casual bowling at Montvale Lanes\, 14 W. Grand Ave. All 
 are welcome for **two games\, food and drinks**\, and any post- or pre-gam
 e hang out. Show up anytime! Questions or comments? You can message Andy M
 ilone on Meetup\, or call/text him at **201-234-9609**.\n\n\\*\\*\\* Befor
 e bowling\, we might stop by the Pizza Parlour\, 6 S. Kinderkamack Road in
  Montvale\, for a few slices. Post a comment on the event page to gauge in
 terest. **After bowling\, we'll definitely be heading to Davey's Irish Pub
  & Restaurant\, 5 Park St. in Montvale\, or The Ridge Diner\, 125 Kinderka
 mack Road in Park Ridge\, at 10 p.m. for some food and/or drinks.** \\*\\*
 \\*\n\nAbout the group: People of all ages\, backgrounds and abilities are
  welcome! We're not professionals and we're not in a league. In fact\, we'
 re a group of people who probably each won't score more than 100 points an
 d will land more than our fair share of gutter balls. There's no pressure 
 at all!!!! We're not here to analyze your form or technique.\n\nMore event
  details: You pay for your own games\, food and drinks. Please bring cash.
  The alley does not accept card. But there is an ATM on site. **The** **co
 st per player is $18 for two games** **and bowling shoes.** If you have yo
 ur own shoes\, the cost is $12. Please try to bring exact change since And
 y will have a limited amount of cash. If you bring a $20 bill and he doesn
 't have change\, any remainder would just go toward the bowling alley tip.
 \n\nFood and drinks (alcoholic and non-alcoholic) are available on site\, 
 plus tables and an alley bar to hang at during the event. There is a dart 
 board and a few arcade games\, as well.\n\n**What do you do when you get t
 here?** First\, find the group inside around the front desk. Look for a gr
 owing group of people! Call or text Andy Milone at 201-234-9609 if you can
 't find us. Once Andy secures the lanes\, please pay him before getting yo
 ur bowling shoes.\n\n**Please know that it is possible we have to wait 20-
 40 minutes until lane(s) free up.** It's also possible that we may have to
  relocate or cancel that night if there's a long wait list upon arrival. P
 lease keep that in mind if traveling from far away!\n\nFor those who don't
  have cars or are looking to avoid driving\, the Montvale Train Station is
  only like a five-minute walk from the bowling alley and can be reached vi
 a the Pascack Valley Line. Last train leaves at 12:20 a.m. and heads towar
 d Hoboken. (https://gmtma.org/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/rail_system_map.j
 pg)\n\nMany thanks to Taylor\, one of our group participants\, for recomme
 nding Montvale Lanes! You can learn more at: www.montvalelanes.com.\n\nHop
 e you'll join us for our 23rd bowling event\, or consider attending one of
  our volleyball\, ping pong\, skating or other activities -> www.meetup.co
 m/north-jersey-bowling-soccer-volleyball
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/north-jersey-bowling-soccer-volleybal
 l/events/314117548/
